<BlogPostLayout
  title="How to play as Colony - Halo Wars 2"
  description="Master Colony in Halo Wars 2 with this beginner's guide covering the Goliath Rush, Skitterers, Hunter Captain strategies, and the powerful Devastating Host drop."
  category="Guides"
  publishedDate="Published on January 31, 2026"
  dateIso="2026-01-31"
  ogImage="/img/HW-Guides/The Colony - Beginners Guide.png"
  youtubeId="ffCs-rFvbgM"
  tags={['Halo Wars 2']}
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Colony is one of my favorite DLC characters in Halo Wars 2. It's really cool that the Hunters get the spotlight with this leader. This guide focuses on a Goliath Rush build, though Colony has many viable strategies.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">First Leader Point: Skitterers vs Living Barrier</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Skitterers</strong> is the clear choice:
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Much better than Living Barrier</li>
    <li>Living Barrier isn't bad, but Skitterers provides amazing buffs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Goliath Rush Build Order</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Base Setup</h3>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Harvester</strong> (first building)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Harvester</strong> (second building)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Power Extractor</strong> (third building)</li>
    <li>Upgrade Harvester when done</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Raid Camp</strong> (fourth building)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Raid Camp</strong> (fifth building)</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Mini Base</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Get a mini base early (prefer protected locations in the back)</li>
    <li>Build another <strong class="text-cyan-400">Harvester</strong> on the mini</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Goliath Production</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Once you have 300+ power, upgrade the Power Extractor</li>
    <li>Start pumping Goliaths (150 supplies, 80 power each)</li>
    <li>Capture power nodes - they're crucial for this build</li>
    <li>You'll be power-starved until Power Extractor is upgraded and nodes are captured</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Second Leader Point: Engineer Swarm</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">Engineer Swarm is fantastic:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Insane healing ability</li>
    <li>Makes your Goliath rush very hard to stop</li>
    <li>Drop it on your Goliaths during attacks</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Optional: Skitterers on Goliaths</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">You can attach Skitterers to Goliaths for more damage:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Increases cost to 300 supplies and 100 power each</li>
    <li>Pretty expensive but powerful</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Supplemental Units</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Build some Grunts between Goliaths when power is low</li>
    <li>Grunts help take out infantry during base attacks</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Executing the Rush</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Timing</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Around the <strong class="text-cyan-400">5-minute mark</strong> is the latest you should wait:
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Opponents may have built up defenses</li>
    <li>They might be at Tech 2 with turrets</li>
    <li>With 11-12 Goliaths and 8 Grunts, you should be able to deal serious damage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">During the Attack</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Destroy one Raid Camp and build your second Power Extractor</li>
    <li>Your opponent won't let this work twice - prepare for mid-game transition</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Tech 2 Transition</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Third Leader Point: Colony Drop vs Hunter's Brand</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">Both are excellent choices:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Colony Drop</strong>: Drops 2 Veteran Goliaths - great for quick reinforcements</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Hunter's Brand</strong>: Good if opponents are making units easy to take out</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">The Hunter Captain</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">The Hunter Captain is an incredible hero:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Extremely tanky</li>
    <li>Has siphon ability</li>
    <li>Can take on entire armies</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Requirement:</strong> Put 2 Skitterers on your Hunter Captain - the damage buff is huge</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Leader Power Options</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Teleport</strong>: Great for getting slow Hunter Captain around</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Engineer Swarm 2</strong>: More healing</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Vehicle Symbiotes</strong>: Buffs vehicles AND buildings (people forget about building armor!)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Fourth/Fifth Points: Combat Repair vs Devastating Host</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Combat Repair:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Heals EVERYTHING (units AND buildings)</li>
    <li>Personal recommendation to get first</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Devastating Host:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Arguably the best drop in the entire game</li>
    <li>Can change the tide of battle or win matches</li>
    <li>Drop zone applies Vehicle Symbiotes to units in the area</li>
    <li>Great trick: Group Reavers together, drop Devastating Host to give them all symbiotes</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">Get whichever you didn't get first for your next point.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Pros of Colony</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Tankiest Leader in the Game</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Hunter Captain gets veteran quickly</li>
    <li>With 2 Skitterers = huge damage boost</li>
    <li>Y ability Taunt is awesome</li>
    <li>Very fun hero to play</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Skitterers</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">Don't add to every unit (reduces army count), but great on:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Hunter Captain (2 Skitterers - mandatory)</li>
    <li>Scarab (3 Skitterers)</li>
    <li>Goliaths (early game)</li>
    <li>Reavers</li>
    <li>Even Engineers (can heal AND attack)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Combat Repair</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Heals all units and buildings</li>
    <li>Passive healing even in combat</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Devastating Host</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Best drop in the game</li>
    <li>Drops grant Vehicle Symbiotes</li>
    <li>Can turn battles around</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Cons of Colony</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Slow Hunter Captain</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>One of the slowest heroes in the game</li>
    <li>Get Teleport ability on large maps</li>
    <li>Use map teleporters when available</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">No Nuke Power</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>No Eradication or Inferno equivalent</li>
    <li>Hunter's Brand is a substitute but won't wipe half a base</li>
    <li>Not as devastating as other leader nukes</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">No Mines</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">If you love dropping mines, Colony isn't for you.</p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Few Unique Units</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Colony was an early DLC leader</li>
    <li>Only unique unit: Goliaths</li>
    <li>Everything else is standard Banished</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Tech 3 Army Composition</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Standard Banished late-game works great:</p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Core Units:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Wraiths</strong> - Excellent, upgrade them</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Hunters</strong> - Great anti-infantry, get infantry upgrades</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Reavers</strong> - Anti-air (5-6 unless opponent masses air)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Engineers</strong> - Essential support</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Shrouds</strong> - Projectile blocking</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">This composition counters ground, air, and vehicles effectively.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Colony Scarab</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Colony has one of the best Scarabs in the game:</p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Why it's great:</strong>
  </p>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li>Combat Repair heals the Scarab</li>
    <li>Can attach <strong class="text-cyan-400">3 Skitterers</strong> to Scarab</li>
    <li>More healing AND more attack than any other Banished Scarab</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="mb-4">Best Scarab leaders: <strong class="text-cyan-400">Colony</strong> and <strong class="text-cyan-400">Voridus</strong></p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">When to Build Scarab</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Not when you have no other units</li>
    <li>Build when you have ~76+ pop of existing army</li>
    <li>Map consideration: Great on smaller maps (Rift), not as good on huge maps</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Example Composition with Scarab</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Scarab with 3 Skitterers</li>
    <li>4 Engineers</li>
    <li>Hunter Captain with 2 Skitterers</li>
    <li>3 Wraiths</li>
    <li>6 Reavers</li>
    <li>2 Hunter squads</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Key Takeaways</h2>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Skitterers first</strong> - Always over Living Barrier</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Goliath Rush</strong> is powerful early game</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Engineer Swarm</strong> makes rushes hard to stop</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Hunter Captain + 2 Skitterers</strong> is mandatory</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Combat Repair</strong> heals everything</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Devastating Host</strong> is the best drop in the game</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Teleport</strong> helps with slow Hunter Captain</li>
    <li>Standard Banished late-game army works great</li>
    <li>Colony Scarab with 3 Skitterers is incredible</li>
    <li>Colony is consistently ranked as a top-tier leader</li>
  </ol>
</BlogPostLayout>
